{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "8f2a1c4e-pf01-4d2a-9b7c-pingfeddemo01",
    "name": "PingFederate + Spring Boot Demo",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "All endpoints for the PingFederate 13.x + Spring Boot 4.1 OAuth2/OIDC demo.\n\nFlows:\n- 1 OIDC browser login  (GET /profile)        — interactive, browser-only\n- 2 Opaque introspection (GET /api/secure,/echo) — run 'Get M2M Token' first\n- 3 M2M client credentials (GET /api/m2m)      — app fetches its own token\n\nSETUP (one-time): PingFederate uses a self-signed cert, so turn OFF\nSettings -> General -> 'SSL certificate verification' before running\n'Get M2M Token' (which calls https://localhost:9031). The app itself (:8080)\nis plain HTTP and needs nothing.\n\nThe 'Get M2M Token' request stores the access token in the collection\nvariable {{token}}, which the Bearer requests reuse."
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "appBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8080", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "pfBaseUrl", "value": "https://localhost:9031", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "m2mClientId", "value": "demo-m2m-client", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "m2mClientSecret", "value": "M2mSecret123!", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "rsClientId", "value": "demo-rs-client", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "rsClientSecret", "value": "RsSecret123!", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Public",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET / (landing)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{appBaseUrl}}/",
            "description": "Public landing page — returns demo metadata JSON."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /actuator/health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{appBaseUrl}}/actuator/health",
            "description": "Spring Actuator health probe — expect {\"status\":\"UP\"}."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/m2m  (Flow 3 — client credentials)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{appBaseUrl}}/api/m2m",
            "description": "Flow 3. Public endpoint — the app fetches its own client_credentials token from PingFederate and calls a downstream service. No auth needed from the caller."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Flow 2 — Bearer token introspection",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Get M2M Token  (saves {{token}})",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.access_token);",
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('got an access_token', () => pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "console.log('Saved token:', json.access_token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "client_credentials" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{m2mClientId}}" },
                { "key": "client_secret", "value": "{{m2mClientSecret}}" },
                { "key": "scope", "value": "api.read" }
              ]
            },
            "url": "{{pfBaseUrl}}/as/token.oauth2",
            "description": "Calls PingFederate directly for an opaque access token (client_credentials). The test script stores access_token in the {{token}} collection variable for the requests below.\n\nNOTE: this hits https://localhost:9031 (self-signed cert) — disable SSL verification in Postman settings first."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. GET /api/secure  (valid token)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [ { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" } ]
            },
            "url": "{{appBaseUrl}}/api/secure",
            "description": "Flow 2. Sends the Bearer token; the app introspects it against PingFederate and returns the token attributes. Run 'Get M2M Token' first."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "3. GET /api/echo  (valid token)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [ { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" } ]
            },
            "url": "{{appBaseUrl}}/api/echo",
            "description": "Second Bearer-protected endpoint — echoes the authenticated principal and authorities."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "4. GET /api/secure  (no token → 401)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('401 without a token', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "url": "{{appBaseUrl}}/api/secure",
            "description": "Negative case — no Authorization header → 401 Unauthorized."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "5. POST introspect (direct to PF)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "auth": {
              "type": "basic",
              "basic": [
                { "key": "username", "value": "{{rsClientId}}", "type": "string" },
                { "key": "password", "value": "{{rsClientSecret}}", "type": "string" }
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [ { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}" } ]
            },
            "url": "{{pfBaseUrl}}/as/introspect.oauth2",
            "description": "What the app does under the hood for Flow 2 — calls PingFederate's introspection endpoint as the resource-server client (demo-rs-client) to validate the token. Returns {\"active\": true, ...}.\n\nHits https://localhost:9031 (self-signed cert)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Flow 1 — OIDC login (browser)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /profile  (browser-only)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{appBaseUrl}}/profile",
            "description": "Flow 1 is a session-based, interactive Authorization-Code login — NOT a Bearer flow. In Postman this returns a 302 redirect to PingFederate's login page; it cannot complete the interactive login.\n\nUse a browser instead:\n  open http://localhost:8080/profile\n  log in as  user1 / Password1!\n\nOn success the app exchanges the code for tokens and /profile returns the ID-token claims."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
